Content:
For all Cosmic Cats holders who are worried about floor prices, the following is my insights on why FP does not matter to us.

An NFT project has a very HIGH chance of succeeding when we meet the following criterias:

1. Doxxed + Responsible founders (imagine them putting their reputation on the line to ensure the best they can do for this project) 

2. A strong community (you can see how tight we are here) 

3. An achievable roadmap (we are already in the midst of building first and second phase). 

We are also going to release a HUGE announcement on mutation. I'm confident that this piece of news will drive up our demand. Let this time to weed out those who aren't here to stay. 

For us, the holders. Remember my quote:
**Trust the team, Trust the community, Trust the process**

A blue-chip NFT isn't build in a day. Good things takes time to build.

This is the time where we weed out *weak* hands to build a **STRONGER** community.

Author: jpsiroman#6983
Content: It's frustrating, totally understand. Truth is, alpha groups with paid services, including bots... it's part of NFT (degen) culture. Here's an example: https://twitter.com/KingdomNFT It is unfair, and it sucks to get caught in the teeth of sharks with bigger wallets. Trust me, as one who has done the analyzing, and railing... and wondering why everyone seems cool with obvious and overt market manipulation... you won't find much traction in changing it. It's surprising, really. And yet, one day it dawned on me: Who says the market is supposed to be fair? What assumptions am I making that gives me the axe to grind? So I let it go. That said, I still find it hard to swallow and thus far have not participated in those outfits. This, of course, is just fwiw. One to another, hoping maybe it'll help you fast forward to the point where you can absorb the shock of finding out that these markets are manipulated and no one really cares. Roll with it, and when you find a great project, the growth and rewards will outpace the manipulation and you'll be set.

Author: WavyTurtle#7914
Content: What’s your personal goal, how many cats do you have, what are taxes like in your country, remember to calculate in royalties, also what’s your plan to get back in for the run up after each large announcement? The only reason to leave an NFT project is if you have an investment you want to allocate more to, and when you do leave a project remember those fees hit so if you buy at .1 and pay 0.015 for gas and then you sell at 0.2 you pay royalties and opensea fee 10% roughly so that’s 0.02 then you owe 30% of the profit to Uncle Sam if you’re in the United States so that’s 30% of (0.065xcurrent Eth price)=$160 roughly and that’s dollars not Eth at tax time next year cause the government doesn’t run on Eth. Just know that flipping costs a lot of money and then you get back in at a future price that you hope is lower…. Not guaranteed though, then you have to choose to take an L and get back in and hope for continued run plus those fees paid

Author: Ritchmo#0933
Content:
Thoughts:
I get why people look at the floor and are concerned with it dropping, but it's important to realise that the price rises in impulsive waves (usually at an unsustainable rate) and then corrects as people take profits and decide what they're doing with they're assets, sales slow down, the floor drops etc, before a next impulsive move. When sales are low even undercutting the floor might not guarantee a quick sale. But beware the next impulsive move might happen anytime (it's a little cosmic) and leave you regretting a low listing.
Sorry if teaching any grandmother's how to suck eggs...

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: Ita all about how you value your cat. You may value it as priceless where as another buyer will see it as the worst of the collection. Its all about if the art is nice and you like it, then thats where the money will be at for yourself. This is the long term image. We gotta remember that we all value things differently, but if we hodl and wait for the right time, then the correct and like minded buyer is going to come across and make you an offer to your liking. I don't really look at traits or anything when doin all this NFT research. I just find good solid projects and cop the ones I like. Keeps it simple, and in the long run, I always know i got the right bang for my buck, cus its the exact one (or similar) that i would be looking for, and it will always hold that price with me, whether it's in my wallet or someone else's. If someone buys it from me then lists it lower, ofcourse ima cop it again and start the process over. It's a beautiful time to be alive. We got big things coming, this is just the beginning for cosmic cats 🙌🏽🙏🔥

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: Guys can we please address the issue of the bots that we have. Legit check this, this supposed person just bought this at .14 earlier today and is now selling it for .09. Complete bot action here. All these Os accounts with no names and random numbers n shiz, 9 times outta 10 they are bots. And fo some reason we always get a nice pump, then these bots overtake and pull us back. I really got no clue on how we can combat this like, but its fukin weird. I just find it weird that so many bots actually were able to mint cosmic cats like. Again some of these accounts won't be bots,  but a large % of the undercutting sales are from bots. Which now makes me think that possibly this boost in sales we had was due to a bot trend run or something. Like a dominoes effect. But this shiz is proper weird, I ain't never really saw no one buying NFT at high price then selling it at almost half its price just a few hours later. Where is the logic?

Author: mike.eth#6721
Content: It's called fear

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: Gn all, im off to bed now, but I hope to see a fair few replies to my post, maybe from someone that has a bit more info than I do. But from my research and browsing this is what I've found. Ofcourse always keep open mindset, but this feels completely un natural. Peace all see yall in the mornin, hopefully cop a few more cats tomorrow too if this price comes down a lil bit more

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: My fren that ain't fear. That's pure and utter stupidity. No one does that. Bots do that cus they need to keep their sales and buys constantly happening. And bots don't mind losing money either, cus the folks running the bots tend to have a ton of bank behind them. And it'll be a group running the bots not an individual most of the time, to allow for more volume to be traded, taking higher risk by taking so many trades then there's always gonna be that one in like 10 or 20 that'll be a moonshot. These guys doin this don't care bout losing money, they just wanna make the major gains, and don't mind taking a few losses to hit it

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: And before anyone says it cus I've just recieved a message saying that I'm FUDDING in chat. This is not FUD, I repeat THIS IS NOT FUD! This is merely an issue that I think we need to raise and find a way to combat, if it really is bots. I'm super bullish on Cosmic cats, minted the max, gave one to a mate, copped a few on floor. And any cat I've minted, has not once been listed for sale. I'm holding these for the long term. This is just something i think we should be addressing and find out if the community knows any more than i do. Cus like I say, I could be wrong in thinkin this, but I do believe there to be a % of bots, which will always happen, but with the way the industry is growing each n every day, there's probability in finding a way to combat un natural sales 🙌🏽🙏 much love folks, see yall in the mornin :-) :meow_heart:

Author: Dr.Greenthumb#8942
Content: Few key facts. Having a game on road map means a lot of work needs to be done. A ton of projects never get a game done. We are already 10 steps ahead of the game by owning virtual land. And we have a rough outline of what we expect our P2E game to be like. We have the ball already rolling on the development of the game, and then not to mention the mutations and the missions. But cosmic cats are already ahead of their time, they have a road map, and are keen on sticking to that road map. Most other places will say that a game is coming, yet some other spaces I've been in, for the last 12+ months, there's meant to have been a game coming. So for here I see cosmic cats as a real investment. Not like these other projects that work off hype. We will see highs n lows, but ultimately we keep slowly climbing with each new bit of information that gets released. Ofcourse with the dips in-between, but this ain't no biggie unless you are here for the flip. I see long term in this project. Not just a cool PfP, I see utility aims and a mission. First stop the Moon, then landing on Mars 🔥🔥🚀
